sunny south wind light boat traffic Loons in bay by
Southwest wind Heavy boat traffic past weekend-some
Northwind partly cloudy- rained last evening- Loons in
calm conditions no boat traffic-no loons on lake today
More jet skis-more vegetation cut up-loons in northwest bay chicks still alive
hazy sunshine- loons doing well chicks are growing- lots of boat traffic
water definately clearer-some algae clumps-loons doing well
did not see loons or ducks today. rain last night
one immature loon no adults-very few ducks
saw one pair of Bluebills- one coot-six adult geese and eight young ones-loons out and about not nesting yet- bass on beds
loon still on nest- wind southwest-85degrees
loon still on nest- geese are maturing- small algae clumps present on east side of lake
loons in north bay with chick-geese by landing- algae clumps one half to three inches in diameter- surface temp 84.6 degrees
loon chick growing less algae chunks
surface temp 74F lots of bass fry
only one loon on the lake- no algae clumps
pair of geese with seven goslings- one adult swan- two buffleheads-no algae clumps- loon on nest
loon no longer on nest no eggs present-two baby eagles on nest-algae clumps by landing- one twenty six inch walleye floatig dead no apparent reason
loon on nest again-one brood of geese(7)- one brood of mallards(6)-no algae clumps
geese are fully grown-mallards with young- eagle young are flying-moderate boat traffic
heavy rains raised lake level-few algae clumps
loon on nest- pair of geese with five goslings- eagles nesting.
loon on nest appears well hidden this year- pair of geese with five goslings
loon still on nest- eagles are getting bigger- one mallard with 10 ducklings- one wood duck with brood

loon chick hatched one egg did not develop-only four goslings now not sure what happened to the fifth one- two mallard broods and one wood duck brood- algae clumps present in the lake water not as clear
loons and chick doing well- also saw eagle and geese today. A few more algae clumps noted- lake showing some green color.
not many fisherman-one brood of mallards-loon chick growing-young eagles flying
Clear Skies- calm wind.  Loons on lake and eagles nesting with ealets.

column1: Loons on the lake with chicklet
Baby Eagle was flying around the lake.

column2: Clear skies- West wind.  Rain overnight  [.3 of an inch]
Mostly Sunny.  Temp of 62 degrees.  Light wind from E/SE.  A few fishing boats.
Warm- humid- partly cloudy skies- windy.  Lake very busy.
Party Cloudy- clearing skies- morning rain.  Memorial Day Monday.

column1: Very comfortable- loons on the lake- a few boats and a NW breeze.

column2: Saturday morning- clear skies- light N wind at 5mph.  three fishing boats- no other activity.

column1: Beautiful June morning.  5.5  inches of rain during the past 6 days.

column2: cloudy- muggy and warm.  getting ready to rain.
Sunny- crisp- fall day.  Calm wind- very little boat traffic.
Beautful June Monday afternoon.  Partly Cloudy with some possible rain moving in later this afternoon.  Spotted both loons on the lake.
Lake conditions calm.  Overcast skies.  Temp. 74 degrees.  Rain the previous night.  Tuesday after Memorial Day Week-end.
sunny skies- high cirrus clouds.  eagles flying over lake- loon on the lake fishing.  a few fisherman. temp in the mid 70's.

column1: some small floating algae balls on lake.

column2: warm- slightly muggy morning.  high overcast clouds.  calm winds.  lots of fisherman on water.  very quiet. 72 degrees and comfortable.
Crisp sunny morning with some high thin cirrus clouds.  Light wind from the North at 5mph.
Beautiful summer morning.  Clear skies- cool north breeze.  1/2 inch of rain yesterday.  Male loon swimming and one boat fishing.
Beautiful sunny morning.  North wind- no humidty.
warm morning with fog lifting to a clear sky.  winds are calm.  one fishing boat.  loon with baby loon in center of lake.

Beautiful Fall day.  Sunny and warm with some high thin cirrus clouds- very calm.  Current temp is 63 degrees- warming up to 75 degrees.  No wind and no boats and two kayakers on the lake.  The baby loon and mother fishing were fishing in the middle of the lake.
foggy- humid morning with a light NE breeze.
Beautiful Summer morning.  Clear skies with some high cirrus clouds to the South.  Three boats fishing and a light south wind.

Beautiful July morning.  Sunny and warm South breeze.  Very humid with high dew points.  One kayaker and one fishing boat on lake.  Lake is busy with vacationers this week.  Water looks better this July than last year from a visual perspective.
Cloudy- warm- humid morning.  very light South wind.  Heavy rains overnite.  No boats on the lake- very calm- peaceful.
cool- sunny morning with some high clouds.  breezy winds out of the West.  Saw one Loon on the lake- no other boats.
cool morning.  fall like temperatures. north breeze
Beautiful- calm morning.  Party Cloudy around 70 degrees.  Will warm up to 81 today.
Beautiful Summer morning.  North wind at 10- sunny and comfortable.  No other boats on the lake.
Very warm- humid- sunny morning.  light wind.  A few kayaks on the lake with some boats fishing.
Beautiful July morning- sunny with light southeast wind.
Beautiful- peaceful morning.  Calm wind- partly cloudy with high thin clouds.  Loons feeding with their babies.
